SIMPLE: impropriate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impropriate
<hw>Im*pro"pri*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Impropriated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Impropriating</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>im-</ets> in + L.
<ets>propriatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>propriare</ets> to appropriate. See
<er>Appropriate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To appropriate to one's
self; to assume.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>impropriate</qex> the thanks to himself.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eng. Eccl. Law)</fld> <def>To place the profits of
(ecclesiastical property) in the hands of a layman for care and
disbursement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impropriate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Impropriate
<hw>Im*pro"pri*ate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become an
impropriator.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impropriate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Impropriate
<hw>Im*pro"pri*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Eng. Eccl.
Law)</fld> <def>Put into the hands of a layman; impropriated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impropriation</ent>⟦br⟧
